Automated System Setup
=======================

This repo contains an installation script to quickly set up development environment on a fresh Linux machine.

---

Usage:

    ./install.sh [options]

Example:

    ./install.sh vim tmux

Flags:

    -h, --help   show usage help
    -y, --yes    skip prompt

---

What it does:

- Detects your Linux distro and selects the right package manager.
- Installs required packages.
- Sets up config, plugin manager, etc. 

---

How to add installation script:

- Add your package name and its dependencies to the 'packages.txt' file. (example: vim=vim-gtk3)
- Create a bash script named after your package in the '/scripts/setup/' directory.
- Inside the script, use 'install_packages' function to install dependencies and write your installation logic.
- Run the installation with './install.sh <your package name>'

---

Note: This script is personal and includes custom configuration. Use at your own risk.
